        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Reinterpretation: Note that the elements sh,gh', g 'h,g 'h' generate sh(gh) -' = 82 and hence all of G (again using the hypothesis that g has odd order, as above). Form the Cayley digraph on s2 whenever $2 = 51* for * E {gh, gh ' Since G is finite, this digraph is strongly connected: there exists at least one path from any vertex to any other vertex (traveling all edges in the correct direction). The shortest such path cannot repeat any vertices (except the starting and ending vertices in case they coincide), and so has length at most G.",
